{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1120,"text":"As a lover of human anatomy,"},{"time":3560,"text":"I'm so excited that we're finally\nputting our bodies at the center of focus."},{"time":7600,"text":"Through practices\nsuch as preventive medicine,"},{"time":10200,"text":"patient empowerment"},{"time":11680,"text":"and self-monitoring --"},{"time":13280,"text":"down to now obsessing\nover every single step we take in a day."},{"time":17840,"text":"All of this works to promote"},{"time":19480,"text":"a healthy connection\nbetween ourselves and our bodies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25640,"text":"Despite all this focus\non the healthy self,"},{"time":29040,"text":"general public knowledge\nof the anatomical self is lacking."},{"time":33800,"text":"Many people don't know\nthe location of their vital organs,"},{"time":36539,"text":"or even how they function."},{"time":38320,"text":"And that's because human anatomy"},{"time":40800,"text":"is a difficult and time-intensive\nsubject to learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44720,"text":"How many of you here\nmade it through anatomy?"},{"time":47880,"text":"Wow, good --"},{"time":49120,"text":"most of you are in medicine."},{"time":51480,"text":"I, like you, spent countless hours\nmemorizing hundreds of structures."},{"time":57000,"text":"Something no student of anatomy\ncould do without the help of visuals."},{"time":63480,"text":"Because at the end of the day,"},{"time":64959,"text":"whether you remember\nevery little structure or not,"},{"time":67640,"text":"these medical illustrations are what\nmakes studying anatomy so intriguing."},{"time":72240,"text":"In looking at them,"},{"time":73720,"text":"we're actually viewing\na manual of our very selves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78280,"text":"But what happens when we're done studying?"},{"time":80960,"text":"These beautiful illustrations\nare then shut back"},{"time":84000,"text":"into the pages of a medical textbook,"},{"time":86000,"text":"or an app,"},{"time":87240,"text":"referenced only when needed."},{"time":89320,"text":"And for the public,"},{"time":90680,"text":"medical illustrations\nmay only be encountered passively"},{"time":93560,"text":"on the walls of a doctor's office."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96280,"text":"From the beginnings of modern medicine,"},{"time":98440,"text":"medical illustration,"},{"time":99760,"text":"and therefore anatomy,"},{"time":101360,"text":"have existed primarily within\nthe realm of medical education."},{"time":106400,"text":"Yet there's something fascinating\nhappening right now."},{"time":109520,"text":"Artists are breaking anatomy\nout of the confines of the medical world"},{"time":113040,"text":"and are thrusting it\ninto the public space."},{"time":115920,"text":"For the past nine years,\nI have been cataloguing and sharing"},{"time":118800,"text":"this rise in anatomical art\nwith the public --"},{"time":121320,"text":"all from my perspective\nas a medical illustrator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125240,"text":"But before I get into showing you\nhow artists are reclaiming anatomy today,"},{"time":129840,"text":"it's important to understand\nhow art influenced anatomy in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135080,"text":"Now, anatomy is by its\nvery nature a visual science,"},{"time":138000,"text":"and the first anatomists to understand\nthis lived during the Renaissance."},{"time":142360,"text":"They relied on artists"},{"time":144360,"text":"to help advertise their discoveries\nto their peers in the public."},{"time":148680,"text":"And this drive to not only teach\nbut also to entertain"},{"time":153960,"text":"resulted in some of the strangest\nanatomical illustrations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159960,"text":"Anatomy was caught in a struggle\nbetween science, art and culture"},{"time":164160,"text":"that lasted for over 500 years."},{"time":169200,"text":"Artists rendered\ndissected cadavers as alive,"},{"time":174880,"text":"posed in these humorous\nanatomical stripteases."},{"time":178320,"text":"Imagine seeing that\nin your textbooks today."},{"time":182080,"text":"They also showed them as very much dead --"},{"time":185880,"text":"unwillingly stripped of their skin."},{"time":189800,"text":"Disembodied limbs were often\nposed in literal still lives."},{"time":196520,"text":"And some illustrations\neven included pop culture references."},{"time":200680,"text":"This is Clara,"},{"time":202000,"text":"a famous rhinoceros that was\ntraveling Europe in the mid-1700s,"},{"time":205360,"text":"at a time when seeing a rhino\nwas an exciting rarity."},{"time":208400,"text":"Including her in this illustration\nwas akin to celebrity sponsorship today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214720,"text":"The introduction of color"},{"time":217080,"text":"then brought a whole new\ndepth and clarity to anatomy"},{"time":220160,"text":"that made it stunning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224360,"text":"By the early 20th century,"},{"time":225800,"text":"the perfect balance of science\nand art had finally been struck"},{"time":229280,"text":"with the emergence\nof medical illustrators."},{"time":232120,"text":"They created a universal\nrepresentation of anatomy --"},{"time":235000,"text":"something that was neither alive nor dead,"},{"time":237880,"text":"that was free from those influences\nof artistic culture."},{"time":242360,"text":"And this focus on no-frills accuracy"},{"time":244920,"text":"was precisely for the benefit\nof medical education."},{"time":248560,"text":"And this is what we\nget to study from today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254440,"text":"But why is it that medical illustration --"},{"time":256920,"text":"both past and present --"},{"time":258519,"text":"captures our imaginations?"},{"time":261120,"text":"Now, we are innately tuned\ninto the beauty of the human body."},{"time":265800,"text":"And medical illustration is still art."},{"time":270240,"text":"Nothing can elicit\nan emotional response --"},{"time":272880,"text":"from joy to complete disgust --"},{"time":275480,"text":"more than the human body."},{"time":277400,"text":"And today,"},{"time":278640,"text":"artists armed with that emotion,"},{"time":281040,"text":"are grasping anatomy\nfrom the medical world,"},{"time":283760,"text":"and are reinvigorating it through art\nin the most imaginative ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289720,"text":"A perfect example of this is Spanish\ncontemporary artist Fernando Vicente."},{"time":295040,"text":"He takes 19th century anatomical\nillustrations of the male body"},{"time":301080,"text":"and envelops them in a female sensuality."},{"time":306480,"text":"The women in his paintings taunt us\nto view beyond their surface anatomy,"},{"time":311480,"text":"thereby introducing a strong femininity"},{"time":314440,"text":"that was previously lacking in the history\nof anatomical representation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320040,"text":"Artistry can also be seen in the repair\nand recovery of the human body."},{"time":325240,"text":"This is an X-ray of a woman\nwho fractured and dislocated her ankle"},{"time":328400,"text":"in a roller-skating accident."},{"time":330480,"text":"As a tribute to her trauma,"},{"time":332720,"text":"she commissioned Montreal-based\narchitect Federico Carbajal"},{"time":336440,"text":"to construct a wire sculpture\nof her damaged lower leg."},{"time":341360,"text":"Now, notice those bright red screws\nmagnified in the sculpture."},{"time":345680,"text":"These are the actual surgical screws\nused in reconstructing her ankle."},{"time":350640,"text":"It's medical hardware\nthat's been repurposed as art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356760,"text":"People often ask me how I choose\nthe art that I showcase online"},{"time":360480,"text":"or feature in gallery shows."},{"time":362440,"text":"And for me it's a balance\nbetween the technique"},{"time":365120,"text":"and a concept that pushes the boundaries\nof anatomy as a way to know thyself,"},{"time":369880,"text":"which is why the work\nof Michael Reedy struck me."},{"time":373480,"text":"His serious figure drawings\nare often layered in elements of humor."},{"time":377600,"text":"For instance, take a look at her face."},{"time":381840,"text":"Notice those red marks."},{"time":384200,"text":"Michael manifests the consuming\ninsecurity of a skin condition"},{"time":388520,"text":"as these maniacal cartoon monsters"},{"time":390520,"text":"annoying and out of control\nin the background."},{"time":393520,"text":"On the mirrored figure,"},{"time":395640,"text":"he renders the full anatomy"},{"time":397800,"text":"and covers it in glitter,"},{"time":399960,"text":"making it look like candy."},{"time":402640,"text":"By doing this,"},{"time":403880,"text":"Michael downplays\nthe common perception of anatomy"},{"time":406280,"text":"so closely tied to just disease and death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411680,"text":"Now, this next concept\nmight not make much sense,"},{"time":414640,"text":"but human anatomy\nis no longer limited to humans."},{"time":418400,"text":"When you were a child,"},{"time":419680,"text":"did you ever wish\nthat your toys could come to life?"},{"time":422160,"text":"Well, Jason Freeny\nmakes those dreams come true"},{"time":424400,"text":"with his magical toy dissections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":428640,"text":"One might think that this\nwould bring a morbid edge"},{"time":431080,"text":"to one's innocent childhood characters,"},{"time":433560,"text":"but Jason says of his dissections,"},{"time":436080,"text":"\"One thing I've never seen\nin a child's reaction to my work is fear.\""},{"time":441640,"text":"It's always wonder,"},{"time":443200,"text":"amazement"},{"time":444600,"text":"and wanting to explore."},{"time":446680,"text":"Fear of anatomy and guts\nis a learned reaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452040,"text":"This anatomization also extends to\npolitically and socially charged objects."},{"time":459360,"text":"In Noah Scalin's \"Anatomy of War,\""},{"time":461480,"text":"we see a gun dissected\nto reveal human organs."},{"time":465800,"text":"But if you look closely,"},{"time":467920,"text":"you'll notice that it lacks a brain."},{"time":470960,"text":"And if you keep looking,\nyou might also notice"},{"time":473160,"text":"that Noah has so thoughtfully\nplaced the rectum"},{"time":476280,"text":"at the business end of that gun barrel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481640,"text":"Now, this next artist\nI've been following for many years,"},{"time":484880,"text":"watching him excite\nthe public about anatomy."},{"time":489080,"text":"Danny Quirk is a young artist"},{"time":491240,"text":"who paints his subjects\nin the process of self-dissection."},{"time":495560,"text":"He bends the rules of medical illustration"},{"time":497640,"text":"by inserting a very dramatic\nlight and shadow."},{"time":500800,"text":"And this creates a 3-D illusion"},{"time":503200,"text":"that lends itself very well\nto painting directly on the human skin."},{"time":509520,"text":"Danny makes it look as if a person's\nskin has actually been removed."},{"time":514080,"text":"And this effect --"},{"time":515799,"text":"also cool and tattoo-like --"},{"time":518960,"text":"easily transitions\ninto a medical illustration."},{"time":523240,"text":"Now Danny is currently\ntraveling the world,"},{"time":525320,"text":"teaching anatomy to the public\nvia his body paintings,"},{"time":528360,"text":"which is why it was\nso shocking to find out"},{"time":530440,"text":"that he was rejected\nfrom medical illustration programs."},{"time":533880,"text":"But he's doing just fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538200,"text":"Then there are artists"},{"time":539760,"text":"who are extracting anatomy from both\nthe medical world and the art world"},{"time":543560,"text":"and are placing it\ndirectly on the streets."},{"time":546400,"text":"London-based SHOK-1 paints\ngiant X-rays of pop culture icons."},{"time":551200,"text":"His X-rays show how culture\ncan come to have an anatomy of its own,"},{"time":555480,"text":"and conversely how culture can become\npart of the anatomy of a person."},{"time":560000,"text":"You come to admire his work"},{"time":561360,"text":"because reproducing X-rays by hand,\nlet alone with spray paint,"},{"time":564440,"text":"is extremely difficult."},{"time":566520,"text":"But then again this is a street artist,"},{"time":568440,"text":"who also happens to hold\na degree in applied chemistry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573120,"text":"Nychos, an Austrian street artist,"},{"time":575640,"text":"takes the term \"exploded view\"\nto a whole new level,"},{"time":578760,"text":"splattering human and animal dissections\non walls all over the world."},{"time":583680,"text":"Influenced by comics and heavy metal,"},{"time":586320,"text":"Nychos inserts a very youthful\nand enticing energy into anatomy"},{"time":591160,"text":"that I just love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594960,"text":"Street artists believe\nthat art belongs to the public."},{"time":598800,"text":"And this street anatomy is so captivating"},{"time":601680,"text":"because it is the furthest removed\nfrom the medical world."},{"time":604920,"text":"It forces you to look at it,"},{"time":606560,"text":"and confront your own\nperceptions about anatomy,"},{"time":609400,"text":"whether you find it beautiful,"},{"time":611680,"text":"gross,"},{"time":612920,"text":"morbid"},{"time":614160,"text":"or awe-inspiring, like I do."},{"time":616920,"text":"That it elicits these responses at all"},{"time":618880,"text":"is due to our intimate\nand often changing relationship with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624120,"text":"All of the artists\nthat I showed you here today"},{"time":626360,"text":"referenced medical\nillustrations for their art."},{"time":629040,"text":"But for them,"},{"time":630280,"text":"anatomy isn't just something to memorize,"},{"time":633000,"text":"but a base from which to understand\nthe human body on a meaningful level;"},{"time":638080,"text":"to depict it in ways that we can relate,"},{"time":640480,"text":"whether it be through cartoons,"},{"time":642840,"text":"body painting"},{"time":644080,"text":"or street art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645840,"text":"Anatomical art has the power"},{"time":648080,"text":"to reach far beyond\nthe pages of a medical textbook,"},{"time":651120,"text":"to ignite an excitement in the public,"},{"time":653320,"text":"and reinvigorate an enthusiasm\nin the medical world,"},{"time":656760,"text":"ultimately connecting our innermost selves\nwith our bodies through art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663880,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665120,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}